#. <section class="sutta" id="sn2.18"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.18:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.18:0.2"
msgid "2. Anāthapiṇḍikavagga"
msgstr "2. With Anāthapiṇḍika"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.18:0.3"
msgid "18. Kakudhasutta"
msgstr "18. With Kakudha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.124"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn2.18:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn2.18:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sākete viharati añjanavane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāketa in the deer park at the "
"Añjana Wood."

msgctxt "sn2.18:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho kakudho devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ "
"añjanavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho kakudho devaputto "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, the glorious god Kakudha, lighting up the entire Añjana "
"Wood, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn2.18:1.4"
msgid "“nandasi, samaṇā”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you delight, ascetic?”"

msgctxt "sn2.18:1.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ laddhā, āvuso”ti?"
msgstr "“What have I got, sir?”"

msgctxt "sn2.18:1.6"
msgid "“Tena hi, samaṇa, socasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Well then, ascetic, do you sorrow?”"

msgctxt "sn2.18:1.7"
msgid "“Kiṃ jīyittha, āvuso”ti?"
msgstr "“What have I lost, sir?”"

#. VAR: na ca → neva (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn2.18:1.8"
msgid "“Tena hi, samaṇa, neva nandasi na ca socasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Well then, ascetic, do you neither delight nor sorrow?”"

msgctxt "sn2.18:1.9"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: anagho → anigho (si, s1-3, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.18:2.1"
msgid "“Kacci tvaṃ anagho bhikkhu,"
msgstr "“I hope you’re untroubled, mendicant,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: nandī → nandi (bj, s1-3, km, pts2)
msgctxt "sn2.18:2.2"
msgid "kacci nandī na vijjati;"
msgstr "I hope that delight isn’t found in you."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:2.3"
msgid "Kacci taṃ ekamāsīnaṃ,"
msgstr "I hope that discontent doesn’t"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:2.4"
msgid "aratī nābhikīratī”ti."
msgstr "overwhelm you as you sit alone.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.125"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.18:3.1"
msgid "“Anagho ve ahaṃ yakkha,"
msgstr "“I’m genuinely untroubled, spirit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:3.2"
msgid "atho nandī na vijjati;"
msgstr "and no delight is found in me."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:3.3"
msgid "Atho maṃ ekamāsīnaṃ,"
msgstr "And also discontent doesn’t"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:3.4"
msgid "aratī nābhikīratī”ti."
msgstr "overwhelm me as I sit alone.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.18:4.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ tvaṃ anagho bhikkhu,"
msgstr "“How are you untroubled, mendicant?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:4.2"
msgid "kathaṃ nandī na vijjati;"
msgstr "How is delight not found in you?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:4.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ taṃ ekamāsīnaṃ,"
msgstr "How does discontent not"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:4.4"
msgid "aratī nābhikīratī”ti."
msgstr "overwhelm you as you sit alone?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.18:5.1"
msgid "“Aghajātassa ve nandī,"
msgstr "“Delight is born from misery,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:5.2"
msgid "nandījātassa ve aghaṃ;"
msgstr "misery is born from delight;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:5.3"
msgid "Anandī anagho bhikkhu,"
msgstr "sir, you should know me as"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:5.4"
msgid "evaṃ jānāhi āvuso”ti."
msgstr "a mendicant free of delight and misery.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.18:6.1"
msgid "“Cirassaṃ vata passāmi,"
msgstr "“After a long time I see"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:6.2"
msgid "brāhmaṇaṃ parinibbutaṃ;"
msgstr "a brahmin extinguished."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:6.3"
msgid "Anandiṃ anaghaṃ bhikkhuṃ,"
msgstr "A mendicant free of delight and misery,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.18:6.4"
msgid "tiṇṇaṃ loke visattikan”ti."
msgstr "he has crossed over clinging to the world.”"
